Vol / Page:  40
Edition:
Quote:  Then they built [in 1850] two primitive toi toi tents or huts and another on piles, called the whata, a place for stores. For several months they lived in those toit toi tents. In April, 1951, my second brother, John Donald was born in mother's toi toi home. [toi-toi]
